column1: A customer can make more then 2 withdrawals/ 24 h
column32:
*Preconditions *: customer account and bank account created.
A customer can not make  more then 2 withdrawals in 24h.
*Steps to reproduce*: Open the XYZ Bank app and select customer login section. Login into the account with valid customer and go to the withdraw subsection. Make 3 withdrawals with the amount less then the current balance.
*Expected result* : The customer can' t make more then 2 withdrawals in 24 h and a message is shown: You can not make more then 2 withdrawals in 24 h.
*Actual result*: All the 3 withdrawals succeed.

column1: No message shown when a customer wants to make a 0 value deposit
column32:
*Precondition*: customer account open/ bank account opend
When a customer wants to make a deposit, the amount should be minimum 1 Euro or minimum the equivalent of 1 Euro.
*Steps to reproduce:* open the XYZ Bank app, select the customer login and login into the app with user name. https://www.globalsqa.com/angularJs-protractor/BankingProject/#/listTx 
 Go to the Deposit subsection and enter the value 0 into the amount field, then press the deposit button.
*Expected result* : The deposit can t be done and a message is shown: "Please fill the amount field with a value that s more then 1.
*Actual result*: You can t make the 0 value deposit, but no message is shown. The Deposit button just can t be enable.

column32:
The customer can login and use the app only after the bank manager will create an customer account for him. After the customer is created into the system, the customer, client, can login by himself into the application by follow the next steps:

Go to the app: [+XYZ Bank (globalsqa.com)+|https://www.globalsqa.com/angularJs-protractor/BankingProject/#/account] select the customer login field, after that, select his own name in the field your name and press the Login button.

The customer section will then show the following fields: Transactions, Deposit, Withdrawal - section that the customer can check, the Logout and Home button.

The account number, balance and currency will be also shown with the details of the moment shown.

Document reviewed was the documentation for the XYZ Bank app: [https://github.com/CismaruAnaMaria/manual_testing_project/blob/main/Documentatie%20pt%20xyz%20bank.docx|https://github.com/CismaruAnaMaria/manual_testing_project/blob/main/Documentatie%20pt%20xyz%20bank.docx|smart-link]

* The deposit/day by the customer must to be more then 1 Euro or the equivalent once;

column1: Create the Customer Login section
column32:
h5. The XYZ Bank app should be both used by the bank’s authorized personal, like the manager and by the customer directly.

h5. The customer can login and use the app only after the bank manager will create an customer account for him. After the customer is created into the system, the customer, client, can login by himself into the application by follow the next steps:

h5. Go to the app: [XYZ Bank (globalsqa.com)|https://www.globalsqa.com/angularJs-protractor/BankingProject/#/account] select the customer login field, after that, select his own name in the field your name and press the Login button.

h5. The customer section will then show the following fields: Transactions, Deposit, Withdrawal - section that the customer can check, the Logout and Home button.

h5. The account number, balance and currency will be also shown with the details of the moment shown.

column1: Create the Bank Manager Login section
column32:
h5. When entering the application it should display a screen with the possibility to select Bank Manager Login or Customer Login.The bank manager login section will be used to create a new customer, to open an new account and to have the a list with all the details of all the customers of the XYZ Bank.

The bank manager login section will contain the following: 

* Add customer section
* Open account section
* Customers section

h5. A customer should be able to login by himself into his own account only after the bank manager has created one for  the client.
